    "His systematic history of Italian art first appeared in an abbreviated form as <em>De la po\u00e9sie ch\u00e9tienne</em> in 1836.": [],
    "Rio used Schelling's theories of transcendental idealism in art, that truth is revealed in art through the unconscious impulses of the artist, and the romantic mysticism of Baader and Johann Joseph von G\u00f6rres as the foundation of his art history.": [
